<section id="command-clearscreen">
<title>CLEARSCREEN</title>
<indexterm><primary>CLEARSCREEN</primary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>CS</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>CLEARSCREEN</command>
<command>CS</command></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Fills the screen window with <link linkend="command-screencolor">SCREENCOLOR</link> and sends the turtle to its initial position and heading.
</para>

<para>
CLEARSCREEN also resets some state that is not directly related to the screen.
<itemizedlist>
  <listitem><para>It removes all turtles created with <link linkend="command-setturtle">SETTURTLE</link> so that there is only one turtle.</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>It removes all completed and in-progress polygons which were defined with <link linkend="command-polystart">POLYSTART</link> and <link linkend="command-polyend">POLYEND</link>.</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>


</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>


<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>FORWARD 100
CLEARSCREEN</userinput>
</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>See Also</term>
<listitem><simplelist>
<member><link linkend="command-home">HOME</link></member>
<member><link linkend="command-setscreencolor">SETSCREENCOLOR</link></member>
</simplelist></listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</section>
